</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C560A899A6F3A9BC09DF918A563B5417" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="description">
<paragraph id="517AFFF435AB3A94EFEA475144B0E82B" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="986DF7691D0BCB90B648BAEF28B18C62" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Perennial with a taproot or rarely annual (?) herb with caudex; stems erect, densely covered with short papillae; leaves papillate, oblong or lanceolate, appressed or somewhat spreading, cuneate, 2.0-4.0 cm long and 0.2-0.7 cm wide; inflorescence a spike; flowers subsessile, with the pedicels 0.25-0.5 mm long, with a bract and two bracteoles; perianth segments 5, oblong, greenish; stamens 6-8; stigmas 2, thick; fruit 1.1-1.25 
<normalizedToken id="6C92FA4ED59FB09ECBF61C0630476DF1" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.9-1.1 mm, with short finger-shaped outgrowths (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3EA37444F3A3B04E00086FF363A7BB06" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Fruits and seeds of Microtea papillosa and M. scabrida: A, B fruit of M. papillosa, enclosed in the perianth (Diamantina Mun., Estrada Conselheiro Mata, 11 Apr 1982, L. Rossi et al. 3322, PACA) C, D seed of M. papillosa (Diamantina Mun., Estrada Conselheiro Mata, 11 Apr 1982, L. Rossi et al. 3322, PACA) E, F fruit of M. scabrida, enclosed in the perianth (Paraguay, Alto Parana, 1909, K. Fiebrig 5468, M) G, H seed of M. scabrida (Paraguay, Alto Parana, 1909, K. Fiebrig 5468, M). Magnification: A, E - 30 x, B, F - 100 x, C, G - 50 x, D, H - 300 x." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.115.29041.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/255658" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">5A, B</figureCitation>
); seed 0.9-1.0 mm, with rough surface (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="ED162E693D8FB5902705F77CA46F5957" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Fruits and seeds of Microtea papillosa and M. scabrida: A, B fruit of M. papillosa, enclosed in the perianth (Diamantina Mun., Estrada Conselheiro Mata, 11 Apr 1982, L. Rossi et al. 3322, PACA) C, D seed of M. papillosa (Diamantina Mun., Estrada Conselheiro Mata, 11 Apr 1982, L. Rossi et al. 3322, PACA) E, F fruit of M. scabrida, enclosed in the perianth (Paraguay, Alto Parana, 1909, K. Fiebrig 5468, M) G, H seed of M. scabrida (Paraguay, Alto Parana, 1909, K. Fiebrig 5468, M). Magnification: A, E - 30 x, B, F - 100 x, C, G - 50 x, D, H - 300 x." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.115.29041.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/255658" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">5D</figureCitation>
). Morphologically, this species is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="0EFE675EA83230F83433F59E35487AFA" family="Microteaceae" genus="M." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. celosioides" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="species" species="celosioides">
<emphasis id="2480F657B2F41C1005DB3CF0F78E1F7C" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">M. celosioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is distinguished by the papillate stems and leaves.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="471B67E9A19BD6116A847A0D734C6305" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="habitat">
